Run time with one 18650 battery- 2+ Hours at full power and then another 2+ hours with the light slowly dimming over that time.
Run time with 2 CR123A batteries will vary depending on brand but you will get about 1 hour of run time at full power.
Works great in all weather conditions. Hot or very cold temperatures will not effect the light at all but temperatures below 10 degree's will shorten the battery run times a little.
No more carrying those big bulky spotlights with heavy battery packs No more trying to use lights that wont reach the distance.

title: For Sale:   VLTOR EMOD Collapsible Stock Black Commercial AEB-CB NOB 223 5.56 magpul colt
postcontent:
The EMOD is about one inch longer than the original Modstock and with the rubber butt plate installed, is about a quarter of an inch longer than the CRANE SCB. The increased length of the EMOD is a major benefit when used on scoped rifles (SPR/DMR), as it increases the available comb for any given length of pull. 

The buttplate of the EMOD is slightly wider and longer at the toe than the regular M4 stock with a noticeable negative pitch, making transitions from the ready feel much more natural. The EMOD was given enough weight to help balance out the normally muzzle heavy feel associated with negative pitch buttstocks.

The toe of the buttplate is rolled under; giving the EMOD a superior feel when the weapon is held in the "out of pocket" heads up hold. The buttplate is covered with a removable rubber buttpad that is molded over a metal strike plate. The shape of the buttplate and the rubber buttpad give a solid stock purchase in all situations. 
The EMOD features more storage in the removable, waterproof side compartments; the EMOD holds up to four CR123 or three AA batteries. There is also an additional weather proof compartment in the clubfoot area of the stock, this compartment can be accessed quickly and holds two AA batteries or other small parts. 

Constructed from the finest materials, the EMOD will stand up to the most rugged demands. The EMOD is available for the aftermarket "Commercial" size tube. Available color is Black. The EMOD is only available in the Clubfoot model.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Remington 770 in 7mm Mag.
postcontent:
This is a fine hunting rifle that can take anything in North America, with ammo that you can still find in stores.
I bought it from a friend who needed the money, and I don't need the caliber, between my 30-30, and my .375 H&H, I have most things covered.

He bought it new last year, and has shot a total of 20 rounds through it. 17 to zero in the scope he put on, one to take an elk last season, and two more last week to make sure it still held zero.
He replaced the factory scope with a great Bushnell 3-9x40 that can produce MOA at 200 yards, and has great groupings at 300.

I am aware that you can find this gun for in between $300-$400 online, but after taxes, shipping, FFL, and the new background check, that will come out to $450+.
It's stocked at local gunshops for $430 or so, depending on store. Which comes out to near $480 after taxes, which is what my friend paid.
The aftermarket scope he put on, he got for $130.
Comes out to $610.

I'm asking $500 or best offer. If OBO means that you think you can lowball me hard, then you don't realize that hunting season is coming up, and this gun uses ammo that I see at Walmart each time I go there. So I'm sure I'll get at least one honest offer.
